The Constitutional Court rule on the UDM's JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court is hearing arguments in the United Democratic Movement (UDM)'s case for a secret ballot in a vote of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma on Monday.A debate on the fifth motion of no confidence in the president was scheduled for last month following the controversial Cabinet reshuffle which saw Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan being axed but it was postponed by National Assembly Speaker Baleka Mbete on the request of opposition parties, to await the outcome of the court application.WATCH LIVE: ConCourt hears arguments on secret Zuma confidence vote